<D>__{and do you know your account number?}
<C>__{sam}
<D>__{yes. 926 31043.}
<C>__{oda mae}
<D>__{yes. 926 31043.}
<C>__{sam}
<D>__{rita miller.}
<C>__{oda mae}
<D>__{who?}
<C>__{officer}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{sam}
<D>__{tell her rita miller.}
<C>__{oda mae}
<D>__{rita miller.}
<C>__{officer}
<P>__{(eyeing her oddly)}
<D>__{didn't they have you sign a card when you opened the account?}
<C>__{sam}
<D>__{tell her carl bruner opened it for you by phone and asked you to come in today.}
<C>__{oda mae}
<D>__{carl bruner opened it for me. he asked me to come in today.}
<C>__{officer}
<D>__{ah.}
<A>__{the officer checks out the name and account number on her computer screen. it all seems to jive. she pulls out a card from her desk and hands it to oda mae. oda mae stares at it.}
<C>__{sam}
<D>__{just sign you name at the bottom on the first blank line.}
<A>__{oda mae nods and starts to sign "oda mae". sam stops her.}
<C>__{sam}
<P>__{(continuing)}
<D>__{no, no, no. rita miller.}
<C>__{oda mae}
